title: sephiran_(fire_emblem)
body:
The Prime Minister of Begnion in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]], and the main antagonist of the latter. [[Zelgius (Fire Emblem)|]], a Begnion general [spoilers]and the [[Black Knight (Fire Emblem)|]]'s true identity[/spoilers], has pledged his loyalty to him.

[spoilers]His true identity is Lehran, a Heron who founded Begnion with [[Altina (Fire Emblem)|]], with whom the first Branded was born. After the Serenes Forrest Massacre orchestrated by [[Lekain]], he loses faith in humanity and plots their destruction via the Goddess [[Ashera (Fire Emblem)|]].[/spoilers]

title: seidr_(fire_emblem)
body:
A character from [[Fire Emblem Heroes]] introduced in Book VII, who is a Goddess from Vanaheimr who bestows a revelation on [[kiran (Fire emblem)|the Summoner]] of [[Gullveig (Fire Emblem)|]]'s ruinous future. Like [[Fjorm (Fire Emblem)|]], she is strongly implied to have romantic feelings for the summoner. She also has a poor sense of direction and often gets lost.

She is particularly notorious for asking the summoner to "make a child" with her.

[spoilers]Seidr is also the person who eventually becomes Gullveig, and [[Kvasir (Fire Emblem)|]] is her past self.[/spoilers]

title: bo-katan_kryze
body:
A fictional female character from [[Star Wars]]. She appears in [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]], [[Star Wars Rebels]] and in [[The Mandalorian]].

[b]Bo-Katan Kryze[/b] is a red haired [[Mandalorian]] warrior woman. [spoiler]A former [[terrorist]] in her youth, she later radically changes her evil ways and becomes a good, just and capable leader of the Mandalorian people due to her royal heritage and vast battle experience.[/spoiler]

Played in both animated form and in live action by [[united_states|American]] actress "Katee Sackhoff":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katee_Sackhoff .

title: ohara_mari
body:
Character in [[Love Live! Sunshine!!]] Her mother is Japanese, while her father is Italian-American and manages a hotel chain. Due to her upbringing, she speaks with an accent and often inserts English words into her speech every few lines.

Mari is a member of the Aqours sub-unit [[Guilty Kiss (love live!)|]], alongside [[Tsushima Yoshiko]] and [[Sakurauchi Riko]]. She is also Uranohoshi Girls High School's chairwoman.

She has [[blonde hair]] and [[yellow eyes|yellow]] or [[green eyes|green]] eyes. She has a [[crown braid]] atop her head, and a [[single hair ring]] on her left.

Voiced by [[Suzuki Aina (voice Actor)|]].

title: power-up
body:
In computer and video games, power-ups are objects that instantly benefit or add extra abilities to the game character.

h4. See also

* [[1up]]
other_names: パワーアップアイテム

title: casting_spell
body:
The act of casting a spell. Often comes with visible manifestations of [[magic]], such as [[light particles|glowing particles]], magical [[aura]]s, runic [[magic circle]]s, and/or a ball of energy (e.g. [[fireball]]) being gathered and shaped in the caster's hand or a wielded tool.

Chanting spell incantations may also sometimes count, even if there is no overt visible manifestation of magic. This depends on context: most fantasy examples count, while people doing the same in a magic-less setting generally do not. Basically it has to be an actual [i]spell[/i] (explicitly or implied in context) to qualify.

title: powering_up
body:
When a character is readying an [[energy]] attack, [[casting spell|casting a spell]], or performing some other act that has a visual manifestation of their focusing energy, usually with the implication that this energy is going to be used offensively.

Not to be confused with [[power-up]].

h4.See also

* [[aura]]
* [[electricity]]
* [[energy ball]]
* [[energy ring]]
* [[light particles]]
* [[magic]]

h4.External links

* "TV Tropes: Charged Attack":https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChargedAttack

title: type_56_assault_rifle
body:
Chinese: 56式冲锋枪, '[[Assault Rifle]], Model of 1956'. A series of Chinese-produced [[kalashnikov rifle|AK]] copies based on the [[AK-47]] and [[AKM]]. Production started in 1956 and continues to be used by various nations today. Easily distinguished from its original [[Soviet]] counterparts by its fully enclosed front sight, and all types are lacking side mount plates for attaching [[optical sight|optics]]. Also often has a folding spike [[bayonet]]. The receiver for early models can be milled or stamped.

h4. Major variants
* !post #6264963: Type 56 - AK-47 clone with a fixed stock and permanently attached [[bayonet]].
* !post #2223228: Type 56-1 - With [[folding stock|underfolding stock]] but the bayonet can be present or not. 
* !post #3173945: Type 56-2 - With stamped receiver and side-folding stock. (two on the middle)

h4. See also
* [[Type 56-1 (Girls' Frontline)]] 
* [[List of Weapons]]

h4. External links
* "China vs Russia: whose AKs are better?":[https://www.rbth.com/science-and-tech/330170-china-vs-russia-ak] ("comparison image":[https://mf.b37mrtl.ru/rbthmedia/images/2019.03/original/5c9de36f85600a44c256f6a2.jpg], asset #21985260)
* Wikipedia article: "Type 56 assault rifle":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Type_56_assault_rifle

body:
Reinhardt is an enemy character from [[Fire Emblem: Thracia 776]] Said to be the second coming of the Crusader Thrud, he is the leader of the Gelben Ritter in the Friege army and has been [[ishtar_(fire_emblem)|Ishtar's]] personal guardian since childhood.

title: nephenee_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Nephenee[/b] (ネフェニー) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

A "simple country girl", Nephenee is a shy, humble citizen of Ohma Village in Crimea, who possesses low self-esteem due to her lowly social status. She's also known to speak with a Southern drawl, an indicator to her countryside origins.

In [i]Path of Radiance[/i], Nephenee is first seen being held prisoner in Castle Canteus, alongside [[Kieran (Fire Emblem)|]], [[Brom (Fire Emblem)|]], and [[Sephiran (Fire Emblem)|]]. After being rescued by [[Ike (Fire Emblem)|]], she joins his army out of gratitude, though she continues to think lowly of herself. She can also befriend Brom, [[Calill (fire emblem)|]], and [[Devdan (Fire Emblem)|]] via supports.

title: at_field
body:
A term used in the series [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]] to describe a protective [[energy]] field used by the [[angel_(evangelion)|Angels]]. It is short for "Absolute Terror Field". The most used form is the "Defensive AT Field", so when it is hit, there is a visible octagonal fluctuation.

The [[lance_of_longinus_(evangelion)|Lance of Longinus]] is the only known weapon capable of breaking it.

title: oogumo_danjyo
body:
A [[Hypnosis Mic: Rule the Stage]] character.

The leader and founder of a religious society called Ito no Kai (糸の会) based in Kyoto.

[spoiler]He was originally a bureaucrat of the former government and had been working a lucrative job, but lost it all after the Party of Words overthrew the old order. He holds a grudge against the new government for stealing everything away from him. He bought up illegal [[hypnosis microphone]]s on the black market and had created his organization as a group that could rebel against the new government. After the events of track 3, the Ito no Kai cult seems to have been disbanded or rebranded as Oogumo is seen trying to form a new religious society in a later stage show. [/spoiler]

title: nina_williams
body: Irish female fighter from the [[Tekken]] series of fighting games. The older of the Williams siblings in the series, she is the eternal rival of her sister [[Anna Williams]]. An assassin by profession and involuntary mother of fellow Tekken fighter [[Steve Fox]]. Underwent a cryogenic sleep between [[Tekken 2]] and [[Tekken 3]], allowing her to stay young in the years between (almost twenty). At first is amnesic after being awoken, she eventually regains her memories. Starred in her own game called [[Death by Degrees]].

title: epaulettes
body:
Epaulettes are the ornamental shoulder pads seen on many [[military_uniform|military uniforms]].  Typically seen in soldiers from the Imperial era (1600s - 1800s). Frequently depicted with a [[fringe trim]]. The term is derived from a French word for "little shoulders".

For the rectangular strips attached on the shoulder part that bear the mark indicating certain rank or division [b]without fringe trim[/b], see [[shoulder boards]].

An item in [[pokemon sv|Pokémon Violet]]. It was written by [[Heath (pokemon)|]], and depicts [[Miraidon]] on its cover. Its counterpart is the [[Scarlet Book (Pokemon)|]].

There exist multiple copies. Heath's original copy was passed down to his descendant, [[Briar (pokemon)|]]. Another copy was given by [[Professor Turo]] to [[Arven (pokemon)|]], who gives it to the player, [spoiler]who in turns gives it to AI Turo. The player can later receive another copy from a time-displaced version of Turo.[spoiler]

h4. External links
* "Bulbapedia":https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Violet_Book

title: albion_(fate)
body:
[[Fate/Grand Order]] character. The White Dragon of Welsh mythology. In the greater Fate universe, Albion is known for attempting to dig their way to the Reverse Side of the World, and perished doing so. The Mage's Association built the Clock Tower over Albion's remains.

[b]Huge spoilers below for Lostbelt no. 6: Fairy Realm of the Round Table, [[Avalon le Fae (fate/grand order)|]].[/b]
[spoiler]Albion is the true identity of [[melusine (fate)|Melusine (Fairy Knight Lancelot)]], who was created from the dying dragon's left hand. The party has to defeat Melusine after she transforms into a black version of Albion.[/spoiler]

h4. See also
* [[Mana Transfer Dragon]]

title: matthew_hopkins_(fate)
body:
The [[fate (series)|Fate series]]' depiction of Matthew Hopkins, the English lawyer who took up the occupation of witch hunting in the 1600s, giving himself the self-appointed title of "Witchfinder General." He appears in the [[Salem (fate/grand order)|]] Pseudo-Singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]], a time when the historical Matthew Hopkins would have already been deceased; however he is not a servant and is a time-displaced living human. [spoiler]He was brought to the singularity by [[Raum (fate/grand order)|]] in order to help facilitate the manifestation of the Outer God.[/spoiler]

title: lavinia_whateley_(fate)
body:
A non-playable character in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s story chapter [i]Epic of Remnant IV: Heretical Salem[/i]. She is a close friend of [[Abigail Williams (fate)|]] and the same age as her. She is the granddaughter of Absalom Whateley.

She is an [[albino]], with [[white hair]] and [[purple eyes]] (sometimes closer to black or gray due to their paleness,) and has a [[single horn]]. Her eyes are always [[wide-eyed|wide]] and have [[bags under eyes|bags]] under them. She normally wears a [[black dress]] with a butterfly pattern, a [[polka dot bow]] in her hair, and [[red footwear|red]] [[shoes]].

Her name is taken from the character [[Lavinia Whateley]] in H. P. Lovecraft's short story [[The Dunwich Horror]], but she has relatively little in common with the Lovecraft character. [spoiler]She was brought into existence by [[Raum (fate)|]] in order to give Abigail a friend of the same age and to help facilitate the Salem singularity, having been implanted with false memories.[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Kuroboshi Kouhaku]]

title: gugalanna_(fate)
body:
The Great Bull of Heaven, Gugalanna was a deity in ancient Sumerian religion and was sent to take retribution on Gilgamesh for spurning [[Ishtar (Fate)|]]. He ended up being killed by [[Gilgamesh (Fate)|]] and [[Enkidu (Fate)|]].

His true form in [[Fate (Series)|]] is a massive skeletal bull as seen in the background of post #4883850, which [[Ishtar (Swimsuit Rider) (Fate)|]] attempts to revive during the Dead Heat Summer Race event. A younger, smaller version of him accompanies her swimsuit saint graph, seen in the foreground of the same post.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[PFALZ]]

title: barbatos_(fate)
body:
The [[demon pillar (fate)|Demon Pillar]] seen during the [[London (fate/grand order)|]] Singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

Has become notorious for being the first Demon Pillar to be defeated during the [[Solomon (singularity) (fate/grand order)|Solomon]] Singularity raid events, where Barbatos dropped highly-sought after materials that players wanted to farm for. Where other Demon Pillars took a few days, Barbatos was defeated within hours of the event’s release.

Appears as a black tentacle with red eyes in London and as a white tentacle with red eyes in Solomon.

title: emiya_kiritsugu_(assassin)
body:
Assassin-class Servant from [i][[Fate/Grand Order]][/i] introduced in the [[Fate/Accel Zero Order]] event.

He's [[Emiya Kiritsugu]] from a universe where the Einzbern House has not adopted the strategy of hiring an outside Master, making him not meet with the [[Irisviel von Einzbern|wife]] he was supposed to meet, and thus was neither separated from said wife nor suffered the frustration of such a separation. Yet, he still became a cold blooded assassin.

Has [[white hair]], [[dark-skinned male|dark skin]], and often conceals his face with bandages and hood. Attacks using [[throwing knife|throwing knives]], a close-combat [[knife]] and his trademark firearms ([[Thompson/Center Contender]] and [[Calico M950]]). Uses the Emiya crest and magecraft for his [[Noble Phantasm (fate)|]], Chronos Rose.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Akira (kaned fools)|]]

title: jojo_no_kimyou_na_bouken
body:
Known in the West as [b]JoJo's Bizarre Adventure[/b]. 

An ongoing manga by [[Araki Hirohiko]], and adapted into an anime series by David Production. The series is known for its references to Western music, bizarre [[Stand (jojo)|]] powers, over-the-top scenes which spawned numerous [[meme]]s, and the [[fabulous|glam style]] of the characters and [[JoJo pose|poses]].

The anime adaptation is known for its use of written manga-styled [[sound effects]] (particularly [[menacing (jojo)|ゴゴゴゴ (menacing)]]), and for using a Western classic song as an ending theme, especially the first two parts' ending theme "[i]Roundabout[/i]":https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cPCLFtxpadE by the British progressive rock band [[Yes (band)|]].

The story chronicles the adventures of the Joestar bloodline, taking place over many "Parts", each starring a protagonist whose nickname is "JoJo".

title: gogeta
body:
The [[fusion|fused]] form of [[Son Goku|Goku]] and [[Vegeta]] after performing the [[Fusion Dance]] properly. Originally an anime-only character that never appeared in the manga, appearing only in [[Dragon Ball Z]] Movie 12, [i]Fusion Reborn[/i], in the [[Super Saiyan]] form, and in the [[Dragon Ball GT]] anime, in the [[Super Saiyan 4]] form.

Finally appeared in canon form with the release of Movie 20, [i][[dragon ball super broly|Dragon Ball Super: Broly]][/i], in base, Super Saiyan, and [[Super Saiyan Blue]] forms. In contrast to his previous appearances, the colored bits of his Metamoran vest are in yellow rather than orange, akin to what had previously been established with [[Gotenks]]. 

His [[potara earrings|Potara Earring]] fusion counterpart is [[vegetto|Vegito]]. Has two failed Fusion Dance counterparts, a fat one named [[Veku]] and an unnamed skinny one that appeared in Movie 20.

title: rex_salazar
body:
Main protagonist in [[Generator Rex]].

Rex Salazar is a teenage amnesiac EVO with the ability to grow and build fully functional mechanical weapons and equipment out of his body at will. Prior to the Nanite Event, he was one of the initial recipients of a controlled batch of nanites. Unlike a majority of EVOs, Rex has control over his nanites and is the only known being capable of curing other EVOs. Since childhood, Rex was employed as a secret weapon for Providence, a global organization dedicated to protecting the world from rampaging EVOs.

Rex Salazar is a teenager with [[dark skin]] with lightly spiked, slicked back dark hair and [[brown eyes]]. He wears a red-orange patterned jacket, [[T-shirt]] is blue on the top-half and white on the bottom-half, orange lens goggles, black pants with blue geometrical patterns and blue gloves with orange cuffs and blue-black shoes.

title: mother_1
body:
The first game in [[MOTHER (series)|]] series from [[Nintendo]] by Itoi Shigesato, released for the [[Famicom|Family Computer]] on July 27, 1989.

This game was translated but unreleased in North America for some time, leaving a prototype. On June 20, 2003, this game was re-released in Japan for the [[Game Boy Advance]] along with [[MOTHER 2]] in a 2-in-1 game, [i]MOTHER 1+2[/i]. On June 14, 2015, the translated version was released internationally under the title [i]EarthBound Beginnings[/i].

title: ana_(mother)
body:
A player character of [[Mother 1]]. Companions with [[Lloyd (mother)|]], [[Ninten]], [[Pippi (mother)|]], and [[Teddy (mother)|]].

Ana is normally the third character to join Ninten, although she can be the second character to do so if the player chooses to have her accompany him before Lloyd. To do this, the player must make it through the train tunnel to Reindeer on foot, surviving all the enemies (4th-D Slip recommended), obtain Ana's hat at the Reindeer train station, continue on foot on the train tracks through Spookane, make it through the second tunnel, and then survive the Snowman enemies. The game progresses as normal with Ana, though it also makes the rest of the game easier as she learns her useful PSI quicker. It is not necessary to have Ana as a party member in order to finish the game.

title: lachesis_(fire_emblem)
body:
CV: Saori Oonishi (JP), [[Cristina Valenzuela]] (EN)

A playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of The Holy War]]’s first generation, Lachesis is a noble of House Nordion in Agustria. She is also the sister of [[Eldigan (Fire Emblem)|]], whom she admires and has romantic feelings for. She is the mother of [[Nanna (Fire Emblem)|]] and [[Diarmuid (Fire Emblem)|]] from the game’s second generation.

In the official manga adaptation by [[Oosawa Mitsuki]], Lachesis is paired romantically with [[Finn (Fire Emblem)|]], who is initially assigned to Lachesis as her bodyguard. Finn is also Lachesis’ most popular marriage option in the fandom (besides [[Beowolf (Fire Emblem)|]]), and the two are often depicted together.

She wears a pink [[dress]] with a white [[skirt]], pink [[thighhighs|thighhigh]] [[boots]], and a yellow cape. [[Fire Emblem Heroes]] modifies this outfit by adding a red [[banner]] down the center and replacing her boots with yellow [[thighhighs]] and golden [[high heels]].

title: igrene_(fire_emblem)
body:
CV: [[Hara Yumi]] (JP), Krizia Bajos (EN)

Character from [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]]. Igrene is the Guardian of Nabata during the events of the Binding Blade, having succeeded her father [[Hawkeye (Fire Emblem)|Hawkeye]] in that role. Unlike her father, Igrene is a Sniper and fights exclusively with [[bow (weapon)|bows]].

[spoiler]Igrene once married a spy named [[Astolfo (Fire Emblem)|]], who hid away in Nabata under the cover name of Gorlois. During their short-lived marriage, they had a daughter, but she died at a tender age. Gorlois would later run from Nabata, causing Igrene immense heartache.[/spoiler]

Igrene has [[dark skin]], [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[yellow eyes]]. Her [[red dress|red]] [[short dress|minidress]] reveals her [[cleavage]] and shows off her [[large breasts]]. Her [[black footwear|black]] [[thigh boots]] highlight her [[thighs]] and create [[zettai ryouiki]] together with her dress. Around her waist are [[multiple belts|two belts]]. She also wears [[black gloves|black]] [[elbow gloves]] and a [[brown cape|brown]] [[cape]].

h4. Appearance

title: class_change
body:
A [[gameplay mechanics|game mechanic]] found typically in Roleplaying games, sometimes referred to as a [b]Job Change[/b]. It involves changing a character's given class to an entirely different one; in many cases, a character's level will revert back to level 1 when changing to a new class, but will also retain stats from their previous class. 

In any case, this tag should be used when a post indicates that the characters present have switched from one class to another, usually involving changing their wardrobe to that of an existing class.

h4. Game series with Class Changing

* [i][[Disgaea]][/i]
* [i][[Dragon Quest]][/i]
* [i][[Final Fantasy]][/i]
* [i][[Fire Emblem]][/i]
* [i][[Seiken Densetsu]][/i]
* [i][[Shining (series)|]][/i]

title: heather_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Heather[/b] (ヘザー [i]Hezā[/i]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]]. A thief from Ohma village who steals to support her sick mother, by tricking gullible men into giving it to her. She’s also strongly implied to be a lesbian, as she will often flirt with and talk about wanting to meet “beautiful women,” particularly [[Nephenee (Fire Emblem)|]], while having no interest in men. Alongside [[Kyza (Fire Emblem)|]] (who’s non-binary), this makes Heather the first openly LGBTQ character in the series.

She has long, [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]], and wears a [[purple_shirt]] with [[purple pants]] and a [[blue cape]]. She also wears a [[grey headband]].

h4. Appearance

title: inugami_korone_(saikyo_tensai_wonderful_world_of_korone)
body:
The 5th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Inugami Korone]], first introduced in the music video for her first original song [[Saikyo Tensai Wonderful World of Korone]] before being made a full 3D costume for her 2021 birthday 3D live concert.

It consists of a [[white choker]], a [[short dress|short]] [[white dress|white]] [[frilled dress|drilled]] [[strapless dress]] with [[layered dress|multiple layers]], an [[underbust]] [[corset]] with a [[large bow|large]] [[back bow]], a [[pink sash]] going from her shoulder to her waist tied into a [[floral bow|floral]] [[waist bow]], [[puffy short sleeves|short]] [[puffy detached sleeves]], [[white gloves|white]] [[frilled gloves]], [[mismatched legwear|mismatched]] [[red thighhighs|red]] and [[white thighhighs]] and [[white boots|white]] [[high heel boots|high-heel]] [[ankle boots]] with [[colored shoe soles]].

Her hairstyle with this costume is her [[inugami korone (1st costume)|regular default hairstyle]] with the addition of a small [[tilted headwear|tilted]] [[crow]], [[heart hair ornament|heart]] and [[star hair ornament]]s and a [[red ribbon|red]] [[hair ribbon|ribbon]] [[ribbon braid|woven into her braids]].

title: armored_core_grip
body:
An unusual way of [[holding_game_controller|holding a game controller]] (particularly the [[DualShock]]) in which the user holds it backwards, with their thumbs on the bumpers and triggers, and ring fingers on the joysticks.

Spawned from the Japanese [[Armored Core]] fanbase, based on recurring jokes about the complex controls in [[Armored Core V]], which required players to hit many of the buttons simultaneously or in rapid succession.

h4. External links

* "The Strangest PS3 Play Style on Earth - Kotaku":[https://web.archive.org/web/20181107205513/https://kotaku.com/5878742/the-strangest-ps3-play-style-on-earth/] (WayBackMachine)

title: steven_stone
body:
[b]Steven Stone[/b], known as [b]Tsuwabuki Daigo[/b] (ツワブキ・ダイゴ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rse|Ruby and Sapphire]][/i].

Known as the wandering stone collector due to his love of rare stones, he is actually the heir to the Devon Corporation and Champion of the Hoenn Pokémon League. His signature Pokémon is [[Metagross]].

He has [[blue eyes]] and [[blue hair|hair]]. He wears a [[long sleeves|long sleeve]] [[black jacket]], a [[white shirt]], a [[red necktie]], [[black pants]], and [[shoes]].

title: zeknova
body:
A [[newtype flash|newtype related]] high-energy mass destructive event from [[Gundam GQuuuuuux]].

<spoilers>It is an exchange of matters and energy across multiple timelines, caused by [[lalah sune|The Rose of Sharon]].</spoilers>

This tag is for the destructive <spoilers>or transportational</spoilers> event itself and/or images with background sufficiently similar to the "kira-kira" in the anime. Despite being based on the phenomenon from the main Universal Century continuity first seen in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] episode 41, this tag does not include that depiction.

title: jigoku_sensei_nube
body:
A supernatural comedy series that was serialized in Shounen Jump from 1993 until 1999. A 48-episode anime was also produced in 1996.

[[Nueno Meisuke]], aka Nube, is the homeroom teacher for Class 5-3 at Doumori Elementary. He is also a skilled exorcist, protecting his students and Doumori's townsfolk from supernatural threats with strength borrowed from a powerful demon sealed in his left hand - a technique he calls the Demon's Hand.

title: badge_(pokemon)
body:
Any of the various [[badge]]s given to [[pokemon|Pokémon Trainers]]. The majority of these are Gym Badges, which are received from Gym Leaders after they are defeated in battle.

The badges in [[pokemon sv|Pokémon Scarlet and Violet]] do not have individual names, but are grouped into one of three categories: Gym Badges, which function the same as they do in prior games, Titan Badges, which are received from [[Arven (pokemon)|]] after defeating a [[titan pokemon|Titan Pokémon]], and Star Badges, which are received from [[Team Star]] Bosses after they are defeated.

title: mochi_trail
body:
When [[mochi]] is pulled or stretched in some way, leaving a trail. Usually while [[eating]].

Due to the nature of [[mochi]] being fairly stretchy, pulling on it will result in it being stretched (ie. a character attempting to eat it, but having a difficult time separating the portion from the rest of the mochi due to the stretchiness).

h4. Examples

* !post #1818431

h4. See also

* [[cheese trail]]

title: shinmai_maou_no_testament
body:
The Testament of Sister New Devil (新妹魔王の契約者『テスタメント』), also known as Shinmai Maou no Keiyakusha, is a softcore erotic Light Novel written by Uesu Tetsuto and illustrated by [[Ookuma Nekosuke]] ([[nitroplus|Nitro+]]), published from September 2012 to August 2021.

It has two manga adaptations and an anime adaptation.

title: mistletoe
body:
A [[plant]] with rounded leaves and white berries. It's often associated with [[Christmas]], where there is a tradition of [[kiss]]ing under branches of mistletoe.

Not to be confused with [[holly]], which is another plant with spiky leaves and red berries. While red-berried species of mistletoe do exist ([i]Viscum cruciatum[/i], [i]Viscum rotundifolium[/i]) they still lack spiky leaves.

* !asset #26707654: Various plants associated with Christmas

h4. See also

* [[holly]]
* [[holding mistletoe]]

title: holly
body:
An evergreen [[plant]] of the genus [i]Ilex[/i] with shiny red [[berry]] and prickly leaves. It is traditionally used for making [[Christmas]] decorations and as an ornamental.

* !asset #26707654: Various plants associated with Christmas

h4. See also

* [[mistletoe]]
* "Wikipedia article":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holly

title: sakuya_sieglinde
body:
A character from [[Seiken Gakuin no Maken Tsukai]].

Sword Warrior. Even though she was the youngest in the platoon after [[leonis death magnus|Leonis]], she had a track record of conquering the void alone.

Voiced by [[Kuroki Honoka]]

title: elfine_phillet
body:
[[Seiken Gakuin no Maken Tsukai]] character.

A caring senior who serves as telegraphist for the platoon to which [[Riselia Ray Crystalia]] belongs. She has a history of losing her companions due to Void. She uses a support-specialized holy [[sword]] (Heavenly Eye Jewel), but was originally an attacker in charge of firepower.
other_names: エルフィーネ・フィレット

title: leonis_death_magnus
body:
[[Seiken Gakuin no Maken Tsukai]] main character.

The Undead King and Strongest of the Dark Lords, Leonis awakens in the body of a ten-year-old [[child]] one thousand years in the future. With the help of [[Riselia Ray Crystalia]] (whom he and [[Regina Mercedes]] affectionally call "Selia"), Leonis begins adjusting to his new life but Leonis also has plans of his own, including fulfilling the wish of his benefactor, the Goddess of Rebellion.

title: riselia_ray_crystalia
body:
The female protagonist of [[Seiken Gakuin no Maken Tsukai]].

Lyseria is the girl who unwittingly undid the seal on [[leonis death magnus|Leonis]]'s mausoleum and nearly died protecting him from a Void; left with no choice, Leonis "heals" Lyseria with the only spell he is certain would work, the tenth-order spell "Create Elder Undead", a spell that worked so successfully on Lyseria that she returned to life as the strongest undead being, a [[Vampire]] Queen.

Voiced by [[Ishikawa Yui]]

h4. External links

* "Seiken Gakuin Wiki: Riselia Ray Crystalia":https://seiken-gakuin.fandom.com/wiki/Riselia_Ray_Crystalia
other_names: リーセリア・レイ・クリスタリア

title: regina_mercedes
body:
[[Seiken Gakuin no Maken Tsukai]] character.

[[Riselia Ray Crystalia]]'s childhood friend and personal [[maid]], Regina is a buxom girl who spends most of her free time trying to elicit a reaction from Leonis who deeply dislikes it (especially considering that this is the first time since forever that [[leonis death magnus|Leonis]] had a human body). She is in actuality the (former) Fourth Princess of the Integrated Empire, Regina Ray O'ltriese, however, due to being born under a superstitious star, she was removed from the family and replaced by her younger sister, Altiria Ray O'ltriese.

Voiced by [[Suzaki Aya]]

body:

title: glass_slipper
body:
A pair of shoes made out of glass, based off of the [[Cinderella (fairy tale)|]] fairy tale where the heroine wears such a pair of shoes to the royal ball, but must flee at midnight and accidentally leaves one behind. The prince uses the remaining shoe to identify Cinderella, since it can only fit her feet.

Despite being called 'slippers', they are actually [[high heels]].

title: phantom_thief
body:
A character archetype also known as gentleman thief, gentleman burglar or lady thief. 

A phantom thief is a type of [[thief]] that steals for the thrill of the act itself and often to correct a moral wrong, for example, a thief that only steals from the rich, criminals or other thieves.

Notable characteristics include an [[eye mask]], [[top hat]], [[high collar]] and a [[cape]] or [[cloak]]. [[Kaitou Kid]] is a prominent example.

title: zahard_(data)
body:
Data Zahard is an artificial character, a young version of High-Ranker Zahard, the King of The Tower, back when he was still a Regular. It was created after the real Zahard stored his image in the mirror using the Mirror of the Past.

Data Zahard appearance was not much different compared to his real self, with his yellow hair, tattoo on the eye, and a red cape. The only things that's different are his fashion, face mask, body height and body weight. Data Zahard is very small compared to his real self. He was portrayed as a young man with ridiculous fashion style. Fans has been calling his data's fashion style as childish and making jokes out of it. Many Tower of God fans and readers has been saying that young Zahard seems like a kid who want to be a superhero and cosplayer instead of an adventurer.

title: oerlikon_20mm_gun
body:
The Oerlikon 20mm [[autocannon]] was one of the most common [[anti-aircraft gun]]s of [[World War II]], used by both Allied and Axis forces on land, installed into aircraft, and mounted onto naval vessels. The latter is where the Oerlikon was most commonly seen, as Allied navies adopted the Oerlikon wholesale to replace smaller-caliber antiaircraft weapons such as the .50 caliber [[Browning M2]] in 1942. However, the rapid pace of wartime aircraft development outpaced the Oerlikon's ability to effectively destroy enemy aircraft, and the gun was withdrawn from service by the end of the 1940s.

It is most often seen in a single mount, though double and even quadruple mounts were developed and used. The Oerlikon can be easily identified visually by the large piston shroud around the barrel that facilitated its blowback operation. Shipboard mounts tended to have a large drum magazine out the top and a curved brace to fit into the operator's shoulders while firing, as well as a gun shield to protect the loaders.

h4. See also
* [[Bofors 40 mm gun]]
* [[Type 99 cannon]] A Japanese 20mm autocannon heavily based off the Oerlikon.

title: albacore_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the US Navy submarine USS [i]Albacore[/i] (SS-218). Character design by [[Kani Biimu]], voiced by [[Tanezaki Atsumi]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[aqua eyes]], and wears a [[black bikini]] as her default uniform. She also wears red [[wristband|wristbands]] and keeps a [[Oerlikon 20mm gun|20 mm Oerlikon anti-air gun]] on her right [[armlet]]. Her 76 mm single mount is holstered [i]on the side of the bikini itself[/i].

She is historically the submarine responsible for sinking [[Taihou (Azur Lane)|]] in the battle of the Philippine Sea, explaining why the latter is fearful of her in the game voice lines (and in [[Azur Lane: Slow Ahead]]).

title: note_block_(mario)
body: An object in the [[Mario (series)|]] series, appearing as a block with a [[quarter note]] on it. Jumping on it causes [[Mario]] to bounce up, and also increases his jump height when he jumps off it. [[Super Mario Maker]] introduces the Music Block, a variant with an [[eighth note]] on it instead of a quarter note. It plays a short musical note when hit or landed on. [[Super Mario Bros. Wonder]] introduces the Marimba Block, a variant with [[beamed eighth notes]] on it. Unlike Note Blocks, they do not cause [[Mario]] and the others to bounce up, instead only increasing jump height.

title: love_live!_school_idol_festival
body:
Love Live! School Idol Festival is a rhythm game released for iOS and Android, based on the [[Love Live!]] franchise. It was published by Bushiroad and KLab and was released on the April 16, 2013 for iOS and June 6, 2013 for Android devices.

An English version was released on May 11, 2014 under the title "School Idol Festival" at version 1.6.

On January 31, 2023, it was announced that the game would be "terminating services":[https://lovelive-sif-global.bushimo.jp/notification] on March 31, 2023.

Following on the success of the game, Bushiroad announced at the 2017 Tokyo Game Show that they would be making a follow-up game, [[Love Live! School Idol Festival All Stars]], featuring the members of µ's and Aqours along with new members from [[love live! nijigasaki high school idol club|Nijigasaki]] interacting in a brand new storyline.

Use this tag for game-original characters, references to events or interactions from the game or when you see μ's or Aqours wearing costumes exclusive to the game.

h4. List of game-original characters

title: paimon_(genshin_impact)
body:
An NPC and the deuteragonist of [[Genshin Impact]].

Paimon is a fairy-like being who accompanies the Traveler ([[Aether (genshin impact)|]]/[[Lumine (genshin impact)|]]) throughout their adventure in [[Teyvat]] as their guide. She met them after they fished her out of the sea, saving her life. Her past before the events of the game and meeting the Traveler is quite an enigma, with even Paimon herself unable to remember it's details. She serves as the mascot of Genshin Impact and is used as the icon for the app, official websites, and social media accounts.

She is very bubbly, outgoing and caring with a love for food and [[mora (genshin impact)|]] but can also be rude and blunt, giving people she doesn't like "ugly nicknames". She has a multitude of nicknames herself, including "Emergency Food" from the Traveler (which became a popular recurring gag) and "Flying Lavender Melon" from [[Arataki Itto]]. Her birthday is on June 1st (shared with [[Arataki Itto]]) which is International [[Children's Day]].

Paimon is very [[petite]], giving her a fairy-like appearance. She [[medium hair|medium]]-length [[white hair]] with a [[star hair ornament]], [[black eyes]] with [[white pupils]] and a [[halo]] above her head. She wears a [[white romper]] with rose-[[gold trim]] and a [[triquetra]] symbol on it, a [[black cape]] with a [[constellation print|constellation]] design, a [[single thighhigh|single]] [[white thighhighs|white thighhigh]] and a pair of [[white boots]].

Voiced by Anonymous in English (replacing [[Corina Boettger (voice actor)|]] (v1.0-v5.7)), [[Koga Aoi]] in Japanese and [[Duoduo Poi]] in Chinese.

title: hakos_baelz_(steel_rose)
body:
The 4th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive English|hololive EN]]'s [[Hakos Baelz]], "officially":[https://twitter.com/yayoiken1324/status/1790300131121872931] known as the "Steel Rose" costume (after Bae's self-adopted [[chuunibyou]] tag, [i]A steel rose trapped in a cage of ice[/i]).

It's a military inspired costume, featuring a [[white hat|white]] [[peaked cap]], a [[white shirt|white]] [[frilled shirt]] with [[center frills]] and [[puffy long sleeves|puffy]] [[short over long sleeves]], a [[black bowtie]] on top of a [[grey ascot]], [[black gloves|black]] [[half gloves]], [[black shorts|black]] [[high-waist shorts|high-waist]] [[puffy shorts|puffy]]  [[suspender shorts]], black belt with a [[wallet chain]]. For legwear, she wears a [[single thighhigh|single]] [[torn thighhighs|torn]] [[white thighhighs|white thighhigh]], a [[thigh strap]], along with a pair of [[asymmetrical footwear|asymmetrical]] [[black boots|black]] [[fold-over boots|fold-over]] [[platform boots]] (one [[single knee boot|knee-high]] and one [[single thigh boot|thigh-high]]). She also has an optional [[fur-trimmed coat|fur-trimmed]] [[black coat|black]] [[overcoat]] with [[wide sleeves]] and [[aiguillette]]s and a [[flower eyepatch|rose eyepatch]] and a [[mouth mask]] as optional accesories, as well as a pair of [[round eyewear|round]] [[glasses]]. Additionally she also has several [[heart facial mark|heart]] and [[cross facial mark| cross facial marks]], and [[red lips|red lipsticks]] - both of which can be toggled on and off.

She has 2 different [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyles]] in this costume:
* [[short hair|Short]] [[flipped hair]] with [[short hair with long locks|long]] [[sidelocks]]
* [[Very long hair]] tied into [[low twintails]]

* !post #7721144: Profile

title: condom_suit
body:
A kind of full body [[latex]] [[latex bodysuit|suit]] with an attached sheath or [[condom]] that allows for sex without the need to open any zippers and exposing any skin, and as such it is common in rubber doll play. The condom is sometimes colored differently from the rest of the suit to make it stand out. Single (vaginal), double (vaginal, anal) and, if the suit has an attached [[gimp mask]], triple (vaginal, anal, oral) variants exist.

For the sake of tagging, only tag those where there is an obvious separate segment of the suit that is worked into the relevant orifice. Do not tag if a character is simply forcing a regular suit into themselves by forceful means. The suit has to be visibly designed for the task for the tag to apply.

title: snake_charmer_(tower_of_god)
body:
Snake Charmer (양식업자, yangsig-eobja) is the one who selects and raises noble talents of the future generation of the Zahard's Princesses.[1] He was the sponsor of Androssi Zahard through her bid to become one of Zahard's Princesses. He appeared as a Data Human that was generated by the hidden floor as the Sworn Enemy of Androssi.

The Snake Charmer is a man with shifting appearance. His golden decorated fang, checkboard black and white teeth, yellow eyes, gray skin, and yellow gold gem on his forehead stay the same. His shifting appearance turned out to be different because he is made of several gray snakes that form the main body.

title: freckles_on_breasts
body:
A tag used for images where a character has visible freckles located specifically on or around their breasts. This may include a sparse or dense cluster of freckles on the cleavage, underside, or upper portions of the breasts. The freckles can be natural skin features or stylized elements depending on the artist's intent.

This tag is often used in conjunction with freckles, nude, underboob, or topless when the artwork focuses on the upper body and skin detail. Freckles on other parts of the body (e.g., face, shoulders) should not be the focus of this tag unless they are also visibly present on the breasts.

Do not confuse with mole or beauty mark, which refer to singular or specific dark spots rather than the scattered or patterned appearance typical of freckles.

title: po_bidau_proust
body:
Po Bidau Proust (포 비더 프루스트) is a High Ranker from the Po Bidau Family. He first appeared in the background when Po Bidau Gustang captured Rachel and Ha Yura, while later springing a trap on the Lo Po Bia Family forces and giving commands to capture all Lo Po Bia Branch Family Heads.

Proust is a giant silver haired creature with two long ears, horns, round glasses, a huge robe and often seen sitting holding a huge book. Proust is extremely intelligent and wise.

title: eurasia_enne_zahard
body:
Eurasia Enne Zahard (유라시아 엔 자하드, Yurahshia En Jahad, "Eurasia Enne Zahard") is one of Zahard's Princesses and a High Ranker, currently ranked 7th in the Tower. After she and her weapon, the Colorless December, went berserk, she was sealed away.[1] She hails from the Eurasia Family and her mother is Eurasia Blossom whilst her father is Po Bidau Gustang.

While Enne’s full appearance is largely unknown, she was widely admired for her gorgeous looks and pacifistic personality.[1] Notably, she is said to have pink hair.[

body:
A [[horse]] or other four-legged animal standing on its hind legs. May also apply to [[taur]]s.

Please be careful to not confuse with [[furry]] - if it has humanoid shoulders, it's not rearing. Animals and humanoids have different body structures. Animals that are naturally bipedal are also not rearing.

title: berserker_(fate/zero)
body:
[[Fate/Zero]] character.

A towering man clad in black-bluish [[full armor|full plate armor]], wearing a plumed [[helmet]] that conceals his face. Sometimes he's depicted with his helmet off, with [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] and a gaunt face.

[b]True Name:[/b] [[Lancelot (fate/zero)|]]. He also has a [[Fate/Grand Order]] incarnation where he fights under the [[Lancelot (fate/grand order)|Saber]] designation.

For tagging purposes, only also tag [[Lancelot (Fate/Zero)]] if it's clearly his original appearance in the Berserker armor or both appear in the image. Not all helmetless depictions of Berserker are his original version. Some of the differences between the two can be seen in asset #23661650.

Not to be mistaken with [[Heracles (fate)|]].

body:

An alchemist who comes in possession of a sentient book named [[Plachta]], and she helps to restore the book's memories. Her outfit remains the same but changes colors in each game; blue coat and red skirt for her game, red coat and pink skirt for Firis, and white coat and maroon skirt for Lydie/Suelle.

title: angra_mainyu_(fate)
body:
A servant first appeared in [[Fate/hollow ataraxia]], being the first Avenger-class servant of the franchise.

While his true form is that of a pitch-black humanoid [[silhouette]], he is usually depicted with the body of [[Emiya Shirou]]. In this form, he has his hands and feet wrapped with [[bandages]], [[yellow eyes]], short [[black hair]], a [[red headband]], and [[full-body tattoo]]s.

Major antagonist in the [[fate (series)|Fate series]]. He participated in the Third Holy Grail War but was defeated. The [[holy grail (fate)|]] became corrupted as a result, turning it into the equivalent of All the World's Evils.

He appears as the irregular Servant Avenger in [[Fate/hollow ataraxia]], replacing [[Cu Chulainn (fate/stay night)|]] as [[Bazett Fraga McRemitz]]'s Servant.

In the [[Heaven's Feel]] route of [[Fate/Stay Night]], he becomes [[Matou Sakura]]'s Servant.

Also appears in [[Fate/Grand Order]] in the Friend Point banner, being a unique 0-Star Avenger. He is considered a "secret character", never being directly mentioned or featured in any announcements or promotional material.

[b]True Name:[/b] Angra Mainyu, the evil god of Zoroastrian religion
[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]] ([[Fate/hollow ataraxia]]), [[Nekotawawa]] ([[Fate/Grand Order]])
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Terashima Takuma]]

title: sterkenburg_cranach
body:
A swordsman who appears in all four games of the Arland [[atelier (series)|Atelier]] series: [[Atelier Rorona]], [[Atelier Totori]], [[Atelier Meruru]] and [[Atelier Lulua]]. He goes by the nickname [b]Sterk[/b] since he knows his actual name is hard to pronounce. Sterk is a knight at heart and isn't pleased when the monarchy system is abolished to create the Arland Republic. Sterk is also known for scaring others with his appearance which often upsets him, and keeps white pigeons as pets/messengers.

In Atelier Rorona, he works as a castle guard and is the receptionist for Rorona's assignments. In Atelier Totori, the knighthood is dissolved and he works as a wandering adventurer, whom [[gino knab|Gino]] fervently demands to take him in as his pupil. In Atelier Meruru, Sterk is more than eager to serve Princess [[merurulince rede arls|Meruru]] to the point that it interferes with her work.

title: x-change_(series)
body: X-Change is a series of eroge visual novels produced by Crowd. The plot revolves around a male protagonist as he changes gender through some unfortunate means and attempts to get back to his male self. The original series had three games produced for it and an offshoot series involving a similar situation was produced by the same company, although it involved different characters. Upgraded versions of the original game were produced by Crowd, but haven't been released in English.

title: x-change
body:
[[X-Change]] is a erotic game series by Peach Princess, where you play a young man named Takuya, who, due to drinking a strange science experiment, ends up being the unwitting guinea pig in a gender swap experiment, which is the source of the title of the series.

The game was followed up by a sequel, X-Change 2, where Takuya ends up accidentally turned into a girl by a machine, as well as a third, and final, part, X-Change 3, which completed the storyline.

The game's premise in all three games, is deceptively simple, that Takuya has to find a cure for his transformation.
This is made more difficult by the fact that a lot of characters in the game want Takuya to stay a girl, and the endings reflect that, with only one or two endings leading to the cure.

The series was followed up by Ying-Yang! X-Change Alternative, a new slant on the series, which uses a different main character and setting, although keeping the concept of the sex-change potion.

title: deirdre_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Deirdre[/b] (ディアドラ, known as [b]Diadora[/b] in the Japanese version) is a major character from [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War]]. She is the wife of [[Sigurd (Fire Emblem)|]] and mother of [[Seliph (Fire Emblem)|]].

[spoiler]Deirdre serves as the cornerstone of the game's entire plot. Some time into the adventure, [[Manfroy (fire emblem)|]] abducts and brainwashes Deirdre, then presents her to [[Arvis (fire emblem)|]]; additionally, she is revealed to be King Azmur's long-lost granddaughter and Prince Kurth's daughter with Cigyun. Deirdre and Arvis are later married, unaware of their relation as half-siblings, and have twins together: [[Julius (Fire Emblem)|]], vessel of [[Loptous (Fire Emblem)|]], and [[Julia (Fire Emblem)|]], vessel of [[Naga (Fire Emblem)|]]. Deirdre meets her end when Julius slays her with Loptous's power.[/spoiler]

Holy Blood: [b][[Naga (Fire Emblem)|]][/b] (major), [spoiler][[Loptous (Fire Emblem)|]] (minor)[/spoiler]

title: the_animage
body:
The★Animage is an original [[mecha]] [[model kit]] series that was released by ARII in 1981. (“The” is officially pronounced ZA/ðə.)
It is based on a fictional anime titled "Chou Ginga Densetsu Bisson." ARII hoped to produce a real animated TV series with "Yoyogi Animation":[https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%BB%A3%E3%80%85%E6%9C%A8%E3%82%A2%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A1%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B7%E3%83%A7%E3%83%B3%E5%AD%A6%E9%99%A2], but the plan for this series was abandoned.
The succeeding series/second season toyline was simply called "The★Animage PART-II."

The comic booklets that came with the kits had serious picture quality issues. [[Kay Mowll]], the main heroine, was ridiculed for "having a different face every time she appeared in the story."

title: ano_hi_mita_hana_no_namae_wo_bokutachi_wa_mada_shiranai.
body:
Lit. [i]"We still don't know the name of the flower we saw that day."[/i], abbreviated as [i]AnoHana[/i].

A Spring 2011 anime by [[A-1 Pictures]] and directed by Nagai Tatsuyuki, to be released in America as "Anohana: The Flower We Saw That Day".

Five years have passed since the Super Peace Busters, a group of six friends, dissolved following the tragic death of one of their own, [[Honma Meiko]]. Now [[hikikomori|a reclusive teen]], the group's de facto leader [[Yadomi Jinta]] gets a visit from Meiko's ghost, urging him to reassemble the gang to help her fulfill a wish so she may pass onto the afterlife. Slowly, they bring back the rest of the group: [[Anjou Naruko]], who remained in touch with Jinta as a classmate, [[Matsuyuki Atsumu]], a handsome top-scorer and his schoolmate [[Tsurumi Chiriko]], and [[Hisakawa Tetsudou]], a wanderer who takes part-time jobs to fund his travels.

h4. Characters

* [[Yadomi Jinta|Yadomi "Jintan" Jinta]]

body:
The [[school uniform]] worn by students of Aogami High School in [[hololive ERROR]]. There are two different versions, each corresponding to one of the two different time periods of students featured in the game.

The present-day version features a [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]] and [[blue bowtie]] tucked into a [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[blue skirt|blue]] [[pleated skirt]]. This version is seen on [[Momosuzu Nene]], [[Aki Rosenthal]], [[Shirakami Fubuki]], [[Natsuiro Matsuri]], and [[Yukihana Lamy]].

The past version is a [[black serafuku]] and [[black skirt]] with a [[blue neckerchief]]. This version is seen on [[Hoshimachi Suisei]], [[Omaru Polka]], [[Tokino Sora]], [[Sakura Miko]], [[Shishiro Botan]], and [[Shirogane Noel]].

title: hololive_error
body:
Hololive Error (stylized as hololive ERROR) is a [[horror (theme)|]] multimedia project by Cover Corporation featuring [[Virtual YouTuber]]s from [[Hololive]], with six short world-building 3D VR episodes, a first-person VR game, and an animated manga series.

The game features original characters portrayed by Hololive members, and the short 3D VR animations have been released on the official Hololive YouTube channel to promote it. Several of the featured VTubers played a demo during a "livestream":[https://youtu.be/WQQAwozBg94?t=2565] about the project.

A demo for the game was released for free on January 7, 2022, and can be downloaded from the official hololive ERROR website. It is currently only available in Japanese, with no planned English release yet. The manga series started on February 19, 2022, and can be "found here":[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL1NeGg1woXqmjylfq2x5E8dA2TUvQcK26].

The story follows a transfer student at Aogami High School, a school at the center of an collection of urban legends and bizarre incidents.

h4. Characters

title: demonion_ii:_maou_to_sannin_no_joou
body:
A 2014 [[eroge]] game by Astronauts/Sirius with illustrations by [[M&M (mickey and mackey)|]].

This is the sequel to Demonion. The nomadic people founded four countries on the once barren Nilt region. They were the [[elf|Elven]] kingdom of Lusario, the Eastern empire Shuka, the ice empire Kilos and the dark [[demon]] kingdom of Hados. However, Hados collapsed due to an instigated revolt by the humans. One hundred years later, the Diabolica were viewed as bringers of destruction and chaos, and as such, they were a target of discrimination and suppression.

[[Caym]] was a Diabolica [[prince]] who survived the fall of Hados in a remote place. A girl named [[Risbell]] visited him and pleaded for him to revive Hados to save the Diabolica, and to avenge the deaths of her parents by human hands. He proclaimed that he would defeat the three countries and make their respective queens his servants.

title: dungeon_crusaderz_2
body:
A dungeon [[eroge]] RPG game by Atelier Kaguya TEAM HEART BEAT with illustrations by [[M&M (mickey and mackey)|]]. The game released on December 19, 2008 and shares characters from [[Magical Witch Academy]]. It's the sequel to [[Dungeon Crusaderz]].

Japanese Title: ダンジョンクルセイダーズ2~永劫の楽土~

h4. Game Synopsis
There is a [[city]] called Glaciest at the northern edge of the continent. The city is famous for a mysterious phenomenon in which people's dream realizes and a crystallized dream called Evil Ice Stone. Glaciest is always full of people who come to see the stone or to investigate the phenomenon. Also, there is a rumor that a lot of treasures are hidden inside a tower, Horn of Revelia, and the top of the tower is connected to a promised land, Eternal Paradise. Allion is a member of a special group that is organized to mediate wars between countries. One day, he and his company are ordered to visit Glaciest. With different purposes in their minds, their adventure now starts...

title: geara_doga
body:
A fictional  [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in the [[Char's Counterattack]] animated film from 1988.

[b]AMS-119 Geara Doga[/b]

A cheap, easily mass produced, conventional [[military]] multi-role [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by [[Anaheim Electronics]] at [[Char Aznable]]'s request and inspired by the original Zaku line. A general purpose, versatile machine, if a bit lacking in the specs department, but good enough to fight more or less on par with the Federation's [[Jegan]]. 

Its shell was modified for two units to serve as Newtype use MSs and piloted by [[Gyunei Guss]] and [[Quess Paraya]] - those two units were then renamed the [[jagd doga gyunei custom|Jagd]] [[jagd doga quess custom|Doga]].

This mecha was succeeded by the [[Geara Zulu]]. 

h4. Related MS development

* [[Messer (Mobile Suit)]]
* [[Geara Doga Psycommu Test Type]]
* [[Psycho Doga]]

h4. See also

* [[Geara Doga Kai]]
* [[Geara Doga (Rezin Schnyder Custom)]]

title: gelgoog_(gquuuuuux)
body:
A mass-produced [[mobile suit]] in [[gundam gquuuuuux|Mobile Suit Gundam GQuuuuuuX]].

[b]gMS-01 Gelgoog[/b]

As an alternate timeline counterpart to [[Gelgoog]] and a mass-produced model of [[White Gundam]], this [[mobile suit]] resembles a heavily modified [[GM (mobile suit)|]] ([[GM II]]) from the original timeline instead of the Zaku.

As a winner of the competition for Zeon's next-gen mass-produced mobile suit, gMS-01 have won its position from MS-14 ([[Gelgoog]] of the original timeline) and went on to replace Zaku for at least U.C.0085, leading Zaku to be sold away for civilians.

[spoilers]One red and white unit was piloted by [[Shiiko Sugai]].[/spoilers]

title: gouf
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] from 1979.

[b]MS-07B Gouf[/b]

A blue, mono-eyed [[Zeon]] [[mobile suit]] specifically designed for [[close-quarters combat]]. It has a distinct horn on its head, spiked shoulders, and a tentacle whip which emerges from its right arm. Notably piloted by [[Ramba Ral]].

A variation known as the [[Gouf Custom]] is piloted by [[Norris Packard]] from [[Gundam 08th MS Team]]. The Gouf was redesigned for [[Gundam SEED Destiny]], and is known as the [[GOUF Ignited]]. It is most notably piloted by [[Heine Westenfluss]] and [[Yzak Joule]].

Despite what the casual mecha anime [[otaku]] may think, the Gouf [i]"is not a Zaku boy, not a Zaku...".[/i] (ザクとは違うのだよ、ザクとは!)

h4. Related development

* [[Gouf Flight Type]]
* [[RF Gouf]]

title: zaku_iii
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Gundam ZZ]] from 1986.

[b]AMX-011 Zaku III[/b]

This cutting edge [[mobile suit|MS]] developed by [[Haman Karn]]'s [[Neo Zeon]] is a Zaku in name only - with outrageously improved all-round aspects, most notably [i]four times the thruster acceleration of the [[Zaku II]],[/i] and loaded with beam weapons all around, it's far from the average grunt suit its predecessor was. One unit was famously piloted by [[Rakan Dahkaran]] before he defected to [[Glemy Toto]]'s faction, and a number of those found themselves in the hands of the "Sleeves" during [[gundam unicorn|UC 0096]].

Succeeded by the [[Zaku IV]].

h4. See also

* [[Zaku III Custom]]
* [[Zaku III Rakan Dahkaran Custom]]

title: zaku_ii_s
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in the [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] TV anime show from 1979.

[b]MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type[/b]

The definitive command unit based on the reliable if unimpressive [[Zaku II]] [[mobile suit]]. While being visually almost completely indistinguishable from a standard model, notably only by its Commander [[Radio Antenna]] and extra [[thrusters]] on the feet area, its greatly superior performance was usually what tipped off its enemies - shortly followed by their imminent demise. 

Despite being very common among [[Zeon]]'s ranks, the most famous unit was definitely the [[zaku_ii_s_char_custom|red Zaku II]] piloted by [[Char Aznable]], "the Red Comet", whose piloting skills and prowess created the myth that his suit was capable of moving at three times the speed of a regular Zaku.

title: zaku_i
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] from 1979.

[b]MS-05B Zaku I[/b]

The predecessor of [[Zeon]]'s massively successful and popular [[Zaku II]] series of [[mobile suit]]s. Commonly referred to as the "Old Zaku", it had a lower output and suffered from overheating issues, but performed well enough against the Federation's weak forces. It was well liked by its pilots, and some units were kept even when the Zaku II was introduced. A number of specialist and customized variants were also put in service, such as the commander type and later on the [[Zaku I Sniper Type]].

h4. See also

* [[Zaku III]]
* [[Zaku IV]]

title: zaku_ii_fz_kai
body:
[b]MS-06FZ Zaku II Kai[/b]

A comprehensive upgrade to the venerable [[Zaku II]] series of [[Zeon]] [[mobile suit]]s, aiming to standardize parts and improve the MS's performance. While still inferior to the cutting-edge [[Gelgoog]] and incapable of loading beam weapons, it was nonetheless a competent machine. 

One unit was famously piloted by [[Bernard Wiseman]] during the events of [[gundam 0080|War in the Pocket]], [spoiler]and it fought the powerful [[Gundam Alex]] to a stalemate and critically damaged the prototype, but at the cost of its pilot's life.[/spoiler]

title: bugu_(mobile_suit)
body:
[b]MS-04 Bugu[/b]

A [[Zeon]] [[mobile suit]] from [[mobile suit gundam the origin|The Origin]]. It was Zeon's first combat-ready MS, and a predecessor to the Zaku line.

Share's it's numerical designation with the Prototype Zaku from [[Gundam MSV]], and it's name with the [[Bugu (g-saviour)|]] from [[Gundam G-Saviour]].

title: zaku_ii_f/j
body:
This tag encompasses the most recognizable [[Zaku II]] variants from the [[Gundam]] franchise. The F and J-type are near indistinguishable except for the lack of verniers on the J-type, which is designed for ground combat. However, the original design of the F-type is identical to that of the J-type thus making it difficult to distinguish the two. 

For Danbooru purposes, these different models should be treated as one and the same.

title: naucrate_(fate)
body:
Partner of Berserker-class Servant [[Daedalus (fate)|]] in [[Fate/Grand Order]] and introduced alongside him in the [[Mystery House Crafters]] event. She is a [[robot girl|mechanical girl]] that assists Daedalus and acts as his interpreter, as Daedalus himself is not able to communicate outside of hand gestures and beeping noises. She can also merge with Daedalus, with Daedalus becoming her right arm.

Naucrate in Greek Mythology is the wife of Daedalus and the mother of Icarus, though it is unknown if the Naucrate seen with Daedalus as a servant is the same as his wife, or if she is simply a mechanical girl based on or named after her.

title: pixie_cut
body:
The pixie cut is a type of women’s hairstyle that features [[very short hair]] cut at around the cheek length or less, with descending volume from the top to bottom. The amount of styling varies, but it is usually unstyled. The cut often includes sweeping bangs that are positioned close to the eyes, creating a flattering and accentuated facial profile. They are typically low-maintenance, require minimal styling, and are a practical option for those who lead active lifestyles.

The hairstyle is often commonly associated with [[tomboy]] characters.

h4. Examples

title: orca
body:
The [b]Orca[/b] ([i]Orcinus orca[/i]) is a black and white carnivorous marine mammal. Commonly known as the [b]killer whale[/b] and also known as [b]orca whale[/b]. The orca is the largest species of dolphin, being part of the family Delphinidae. (Delphinidae is within the Odontoceti or toothed whales, which is within the Cetacea or whales, so orcas are whales in the sense that all dolphins are whales.)

Despite this, works portraying an Orca [b]ought not[/b] be tagged as [[whale]].

Usually growing around 5-8 meters long, orcas are known to be apex predators of the sea, as they have no natural predators.

title: yuria_shardet
body:
Character of [[Endro!]]

Generally referred to as "Yuusha" (meaning hero but actually coming from her name), she insists that her class is "hero" even though such a thing only exists when there is a demon lord to slay.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[pink hair]] tied into [[low twintails]] with an [[ahoge]] and a [[hair flower|floral]] [[hairclip]].

Her upper body outfit consists of protection of her shoulders and neck, with upper body armour that resembles a [[breastplate]] on top but a pink babydoll underneath, and leaves her [[navel]] exposed, connected to her [[shoulder armor]] with a strap with a [[buckle]] on it on each side. She also wears [[brown gloves]].

Her lower body outfit consists primarily of a [[frilled skirt|frilled]] pinkish-[[red skirt]] with protective plates on the front, back and sides, with [[brown thighhighs]] underneath her [[white boots|white]] [[knee boots|knee-length]] [[armored boots]]/[[greaves]].

She wields a [[sword]] with a red blade as her weapon.
other_names: ユーリア・シャルデット

title: humpback_whale
body:
The Humpback [[whale]] (Megaptera novaeangliae) is a species of baleen whale. It is one of the larger rorqual (a section of baleen whales) species, with adults ranging in length from 12–16 m (39–52 ft) and weighing around 25–30 t (28–33 short tons). 
The humpback has a distinctive body shape, with long pectoral fins and a knobbly head. 
It is known for breaching and other distinctive surface behaviors.

title: icarly
body:
iCarly is an American teen sitcom created by Dan Schneider, which originally aired on [[Nickelodeon]] from September 8, 2007, to November 23, 2012. The series tells the story of Carly Shay (Miranda Cosgrove), a teenager who creates and hosts her own web show called iCarly with her best friends, Sam and Freddie (Jennette McCurdy and Nathan Kress) in the apartment loft that she and her older brother, Spencer (Jerry Trainor) live in. As the web show quickly becomes an internet phenomenon, the characters are tasked with balancing their normal teenage lives with the wacky situations their newfound fame lands them in. By the fourth season, their school friend, Gibby (Noah Munck) also works with them on the web show.

h4. See also

title: puzzle_&_dragons
body:
[b]Puzzle & Dragons[/b] (パズル&ドラゴンズ [i]Pazuru Ando Doragonzu[/i]) is a Japanese mobile game developed by GungHo Online Entertainment. The Japanese title is often shortened to パズドラ ([i]Pazudora[/i]), while the English title is often shortened to PAD.

The gameplay consists of the player going through dungeons (there are regular dungeons, special dungeons, and technical dungeons) and battling monsters and bosses via matching element tiles to attack and/or heal in order to earn various in-game currencies. Beating dungeons eventually gives enough experience points to allow the player to level up so their rank, stamina, team cost, and monster box capacity may increase. Another factor of gameplay is the player collecting, fusing, and evolving their monsters in order to make them stronger. Utilizing monster abilities and stats is vital to the gameplay, especially later on in the game.

There are approximately 1400 and counting unique monsters that can be collected by the player. These range from traditional [[dragon|dragons]], [[demon|demons]], [[ogre|ogres]], [[goblin|goblins]], and [[knight|knights]] to mythological figures from various real world cultures and religions, fictionalized versions of popular historical figures, and even third party fictional characters.

[[crossover|The game also does various collaborations with several anime and video game properties]] which are usually Japanese only. Many collaborations have been released to the international editions, however.

There have been a few anime adaptations of the game "Puzzle & Dragons x (Cross)":https://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/anime/pad-x/ in 2016 and "PazuDora":https://anime-pad.com/index.html in 2018.

h4. See also

* [[List of Puzzle & Dragons Characters]]
* [[Emil Chronicle Online]]

h4. External links

* "Wiki of official artists":https://w.atwiki.jp/pzdr_illust/
* "Wikipedia: Puzzle & Dragons":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puzzle_%26_Dragons

title: good_burger
body:
[b]Good Burger[/b] is a 1997 teen comedy movie starring Kenan Thompson and Kel Mitchell. The movie is based on the "Good Burger" sketch from the [[Nickelodeon]] variety series All That.

The movie follows Dexter Reed(Kenan) a teenage slacker who is forced to get a summer job after crashing his teacher's car in order to pay for the damages. He later works at the Good Burger restaurant, where he befriends Ed(Kel), a dimwitted but well-meaning cashier. When the new rival Mondo Burger restaurant threatens to drive Good Burger out of business, Dexter and Ed work together to save their restaurant.

Despite mixed reviews, the movie was well liked by fans which the movie continues to have a cult following. A sequel, titled [b]Good Burger 2[/b] was released in 2023 on Paramount+ with Kenan and Kel reprising their roles.

title: ayra_(fire_emblem)
body:
Ayra is a [[black hair|black-haired]] swordswoman from the first generation of [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of The Holy War]]. Ayra holds the honor of being the first Swordmaster in the series, as well as being the first 'true' member of the [[Navarre (Fire Emblem)|]] archetype. She is vehemently protective of her half-nephew [[Shannan (Fire Emblem)|]], the only child of her brother Mariccle, the Isaachian crown prince.

Together with one of several first-generation men, she can have two children: [[Larcei (Fire Emblem)|]], her daughter, who can be told apart from her mother by her shorter hair and dress, as well as her armor having a gold trim; and [[Scathach (fire emblem)|]], her son. Her children are twins.

title: seliph_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Seliph Baldos Chalphy[/b] is the second main protagonist of [[Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War]]. As the son of [[sigurd_(fire_emblem)|Sigurd]] and his wife [[deirdre_(fire_emblem)|Deirdre]], Seliph is a full-blooded descendant of Crusader [[Baldr (Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War)|]] with partial [[Naga (Fire Emblem)|]] blood. He serves as the main Lord character of the second generation, succeeding his father Sigurd and finishing what he started.

Seliph inherits the legendary weapon [[Tyrfing (Fire Emblem)|Tyrfing]] from Sigurd in the final years of the war with the Granvalle Empire.

Holy Blood: [b][[Baldr (Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War)|]][/b] (major), [[Naga (Fire Emblem)|]] (minor)

title: hizaki_kureha
body:
Sailor Ignis, whose real name is Kureha Hizaki, is a character from [[sailor_element]].

Kureha is a cheerful and energetic mood-maker, always brightening up those around her. 

While she can be a bit headstrong, she is also flexible and adaptable. 

Gifted with excellent athletic ability and a great figure, she stands out among her peers. 

Her strong sense of justice and genuine personality make her especially popular with other girls. 

When she transforms, she becomes Sailor Ignis, the warrior who commands the power of fire.

title: mizushima_aoi
body:
Sailor Aqua, whose real name is Aoi Mizushima, is a character from [[sailor_element]].

Aoi is a gentle and polite girl, always speaking with grace and courtesy. 

She is cheerful and approachable, able to interact warmly with anyone. 

Her academic performance is excellent, earning her the trust and admiration of her teachers. 

She is also well-liked by boys, not only for her attractive appearance but also for her well-hidden, voluptuous figure. 

When she transforms, she becomes Sailor Aqua, the warrior who commands the power of water.

title: highschool_of_the_dead
body:
"学園黙示録 High School of the Dead" ("[i]Gakuen Mokushiroku[/i] High School of the Dead", "Academy Apocalypse") is a zombie apocalypse-themed manga series written by the late Sato Daisuke and illustrated by [[Satou Shouji]].

It is set during a worldwide pandemic that transforms most of the population into zombie-like creatures, constantly referred to as "them." The story revolves around a group of high school students and the school nurse and their pursuit of salvation from the outbreak of "them."

An anime adaption aired in 2010.

title: udagawa_ako
body:
The drummer of the band [[roselia_(bang_dream!)|Roselia]] in [[BanG Dream!]]. She is a third-year middle schooler with [[red eyes]], curly [[purple_hair|purple]] [[twintails]] (sometimes curly enough to count as [[twin drills]] instead), and [[chuunibyou]] tendencies. Her birthday is July 3rd.  

[[Udagawa Tomoe]] is her older sister.

Voiced by [[Sakuragawa Megu]]

title: unlikely_accident
body:
An [[accident]] that is unlikely to occur, usually because it seems impossible or defies all logic. Often, a [[wardrobe malfunction]] that makes you think "how is that even possible!?":[/pools/2553]

In Japanese, this concept is covered by the idea of "ハプニング" / or a "happening".

h4. See also

* [[accidental exposure]]
* [[assisted exposure]]
* [[assisted sex]]
* [[dressing]] / [[undressing]]
* [[nipple slip]]
* [[one breast out]]
* [[popped button]]
* [[torn clothes]]
* [[wardrobe malfunction]]
* [[wardrobe error]] - for when clothes are worn incorrectly, but not malfunctioning
* [[oversized clothes]] / [[undersized clothes]]

title: toyama_asuka
body:
A character from [[BanG Dream!]].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. 
In some cases, she wearing [[haneoka school uniform]].

[[Toyama Kasumi]]'s younger sister.

Voiced by [[Ozaki Yuka]].

title: kurata_mashiro
body:
A first-year transfer student at Tsukinomori Girls' Academy, and the lead singer and lyricist of [[Morfonica]] in [[BanG Dream!]].   She has [[blue_eyes|light blue eyes]] and [[medium_hair|shoulder-length]] [[white hair]].  Her birthday is February 19.

Voiced by [[Shindou Amane]]

title: asahi_rokka
body:
The [[guitar|guitarist]] of [[RAISE A SUILEN]] in [[BanG Dream!]]. Her stage name is LOCK (ロック). 

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair]], [[green eyes]]. Depending on the situation, she has [[glasses]] ([[black-framed eyewear]]), [[red scrunchie]], [[haneoka school uniform]].

Voiced by [[Kohara Riko]].

title: sensei_haruki_suetsugu_(style)
body: Images that are done in [[sensei haruki suetsugu|Haruki Suetsugu]]'s artstyle, known mostly for [[Mega Man X (series)|]] and [[The Legend of Zelda]] artwork.

title: tanaka_(precure)
body: Tanaka, also known as Tanakhan is a fairy from KirakiLand who appears in [[Kimi to Idol Precure]]. He is Idol Pretty Cure's manager, and works part time at Cafe Glitter.

title: bieko_(disgaea)
body:
[[Makai Senki Disgaea 6]] character. [[zed (disgaea)|Zed]]'s younger sister, a kindhearted zombie girl who dreams of being a doctor.

Voiced by [[Kohara Riko]]
